When using the terminal REPL with LSP-based completions (e.g., Python with Pylance), backspacing past trigger characters like `.` would not update the suggestion list, causing suggestions to remain stuck on the previous completion state.

## Problem

1. User types `import os` in Python REPL and presses Enter
2. User types `os.` - this triggers suggestions for `os` properties/methods
3. User hits backspace to remove the `.` - leaving just `os`
4. **Bug**: Suggestions remain stuck showing `os.` completions instead of updating to show `os` completions

## Root Cause

The backspacing logic in `SuggestAddon._sync()` only checked for directory separators (`\` and `/`) when determining whether to refresh suggestions:

```typescript
if (this._isFilteringDirectories && char.match(/[\\\/]$/)) {
    sent = this._requestTriggerCharQuickSuggestCompletions();
}
```

This missed other important trigger characters like `.` that are commonly used by LSP providers.

## Solution

Extended the backspacing logic to check all provider trigger characters, not just directory separators. The fix:

- Maintains existing directory separator logic for compatibility
- Adds comprehensive checking of all completion provider trigger characters
- Ensures consistency with forward-typing logic that already checks all trigger characters
- Only triggers when the suggestion widget is already visible to avoid unnecessary requests

```typescript
// Check all provider trigger characters when backspacing
if (!sent) {
    for (const provider of this._terminalCompletionService.providers) {
        if (!provider.triggerCharacters) {
            continue;
        }
        for (const triggerChar of provider.triggerCharacters) {
            if (char === triggerChar) {
                sent = this._requestTriggerCharQuickSuggestCompletions();
                break;
            }
        }
        if (sent) {
            break;
        }
    }
}
```

This ensures that backspacing past any trigger character (`.`, ` `, `-`, etc.) will properly refresh the suggestion list to match the new input state.

Fixes #258678.

